CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 15, 1941, pg. 24 reads: "Pittsburgh Beauty In Striking Pose - Miss Eunice Howard, 8138 Perchment street, Pittsburgh, may attend Oberlin College in fall. She is a member of the Windsor club and is an outstanding senior at Westinghouse high school.  Here she is pictured in a striking and unusual pose. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Eunice Howard wearing dark short sleeved dress seated on light colored circle, in front of dark background, in Harris Studio
